{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make parental alienation a criminal offence",
        "additional_details": "It was reported that parental alienating behaviours affect around 59% of separated families in the UK, and can be linked to child anxiety, depression, and long-term trauma. Many children grow up without a loving bond to one parent. We feel it remains unrecognised in law. Making it a criminal offence could protect children\u2019s mental health, hold abusers accountable, and preserve the right of every child to love and be loved by both parents.",
        "background": "We want the Government to make Parental Alienation a criminal offence. We believe deliberately turning a child against a loving parent is emotional abuse. The law should make it an offence, train professionals to identify it, and hold offenders accountable to protect children\u2019s rights.",
